{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jon|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"The word of the Lord came to Jonah a second time:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"“Get up! Go to the great city of Nineveh and preach the message that I tell you.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"Jonah got up and went to Nineveh according to the Lord’s command.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"Jonah set out on the first day of his walk in the city and proclaimed, “In forty days Nineveh will be demolished!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"Then the people of Nineveh believed God. They proclaimed a fast and dressed in sackcloth —from the greatest of them to the least.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"When word reached the king of Nineveh, he got up from his throne, took off his royal robe, covered himself with sackcloth, and sat in ashes.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"Then he issued a decree in Nineveh:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"Furthermore, both people and animals must be covered with sackcloth, and everyone must call out earnestly to God. Each must turn from his evil ways and from his wrongdoing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"Who knows? God may turn and relent; he may turn from his burning anger so that we will not perish.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","bookOrder":31,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"God saw their actions —that they had turned from their evil ways —so God relented from the disaster he had threatened them with. And he did not do it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jon","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,6,8,10],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Jonah’s Preaching"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The word of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" came to Jonah a second time: "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jnh 1:1","book":"Jon","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jnh 1:1","book":"Jon","chapter":1,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Get up! Go to the great city of Nineveh "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Zp 2:13","book":"Zep","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and preach "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 1:17","book":"Jer","chapter":1,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 2:7","book":"Ezk","chapter":2,"verse":7,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" the message that I tell you.” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Zp 2:13","book":"Zep","chapter":2,"verse":13},{"label":"Jr 1:17","book":"Jer","chapter":1,"verse":17},{"label":"Ezk 2:7","book":"Ezk","chapter":2,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jonah got up and went to Nineveh according to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s command."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jonah set out on the first day of his walk in the city and proclaimed, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:26","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":26,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 12:41","book":"Mat","chapter":12,"verse":41,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 11:32","book":"Luk","chapter":11,"verse":32,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" “In forty days Nineveh will be demolished!” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 18:26","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":26},{"label":"Mt 12:41","book":"Mat","chapter":12,"verse":41},{"label":"Lk 11:32","book":"Luk","chapter":11,"verse":32}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then the people of Nineveh believed God. They proclaimed a fast "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dn 9:3","book":"Dan","chapter":9,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jl 1:14","book":"Jol","chapter":1,"verse":14,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and dressed in sackcloth —from the greatest of them to the least."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dn 9:3","book":"Dan","chapter":9,"verse":3},{"label":"Jl 1:14","book":"Jol","chapter":1,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When word reached the king of Nineveh, he got up from his throne, took off his royal robe, covered himself with sackcloth, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 21:27","book":"1Ki","chapter":21,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Est 4:1–4","book":"Est","chapter":4,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 6:26","book":"Jer","chapter":6,"verse":26,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 27:30–31","book":"Ezk","chapter":27,"verse":30,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" and sat in ashes. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 21:27","book":"1Ki","chapter":21,"verse":27},{"label":"Est 4:1–4","book":"Est","chapter":4,"verse":1},{"label":"Jr 6:26","book":"Jer","chapter":6,"verse":26},{"label":"Ezk 27:30–31","book":"Ezk","chapter":27,"verse":30}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then he issued a decree "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 20:3","book":"2Ch","chapter":20,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezr 8:21","book":"Ezr","chapter":8,"verse":21,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" in Nineveh:"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Ch 20:3","book":"2Ch","chapter":20,"verse":3},{"label":"Ezr 8:21","book":"Ezr","chapter":8,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jon:3:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Furthermore, both people and animals must be covered with sackcloth, and everyone must call out earnestly to God. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 130:1","book":"Psa","chapter":130,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jnh 1:6","book":"Jon","chapter":1,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jnh 1:14","book":"Jon","chapter":1,"verse":14,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Each must turn from his evil ways "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 1:16–19","book":"Isa","chapter":1,"verse":16,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 55:6–7","book":"Isa","chapter":55,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 18:11","book":"Jer","chapter":18,"verse":11,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" and from his wrongdoing. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or injustice, or violence"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 130:1","book":"Psa","chapter":130,"verse":